race.comment: FROSTED IN TIME (1) couldn't have been much more impressive last start winning his maiden by 9 lengths at Kilmore having started hard in the market in a strongly run, high rating maiden at Echuca first up, where the form has worked out very well. He looks very progressive and really should be winning again. HIATUS (6) resumed with a solid run here over 1000m having shown good ability last time in, fifth in a listed race the highlight. Fitter now and the rise in trip suits. DEMARCATE (2) is a lightly raced type who blew the cobwebs off fresh in a 955m race at Cranbourne, not far away. Suspect he can improve over this trip for the Hayes yard. TORVEGA (7) is racing well this time in and should be thereabouts once more.
